Always referring to himself in the 3rd person, Coach believes in shouting first and asking questions later – said Coach.\n\nABILITY: Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed.
Straight outta Centre Court, Lady Grenade's preferred greeting is a savage chest bump she likes to call the Grand Slam.\n\nABILITY: Serves up a volley of grenades.
Notorious for a' firin' his laser, B.I.G. also loves to read archaeology novels while imprisoned inside the robot dinosaur.\n\nABILITY: Jumps forward and lands with a S.T.O.M.P.
Being raised by bears gave Bearman a unique perspective on life, but he never learned to talk so no one knows what it is.\n\nABILITY: Charges forward, smashing through and into things.
From the safety of her weird egg tank, Mother runs her tech startup. It takes a bold CEO to add a cannon to their office.\n\nABILITY: Hires a couple of loyal Henchmen.
Boosts your units' attack speed and move speed with words of encouragement, delivered in an uplifting tone.
Heals your units with some sort of green energy... and a 5-step healing program! Expect more emotionally stable troops after use.
Show that you mean business by pulling an object out of orbit and landing it on the enemy! Deals HUGE damage in a large area.
Makes your units invisible for a few seconds, even while attacking. Everyone's a ninja!
Drop an arcade machine on them like a total rockstar. Damages enemy units in a small area and destroys obstacles.
Drops two Troopers on the enemy. Hawaiian shirts and hairy legs falling from the sky – geronimo!
Freezes enemy units and sends a chilling message: someone left the fridge door open overnight and the yogurt has gone bad...
Bread and butter of warfare! Attacks air and ground at short range. Cool under pressure, but watch out for grenades!
Put them at the front to soak up damage with their riot shields – but really it's their healthy skepticism that keeps them safe.
Ex-baseball pitcher putting those throwing skills to good use! Medium range and best against groups of enemies.
This absolute unit crushes obstacles in its path and deals area damage at medium range. Also works part-time for a rideshare company.
Deals long range, area damage to both air and ground units – plus extra damage to buildings! Previously a world champion arm wrestler.
It's a building-targeting Gorilla with a GIANT wrench! Why did they make a wrench this big? What does he do with it? So many questions...
Fast moving, medium ranged and can fly over obstacles. Can't be targeted by certain troops or defenses. Blue hair is the new pink!
Eyebrow model by day, Hotshot by night. He moves fast and blasts anything in front of him. His shotgun doubles as a selfie stick.
His attack passes through and damages all enemies in its path! This makes him terrifying beyond the capacity for rational thought.
The van parks up, then the Plumbers pile out – like an army of handyman ants who won't fix your pipes.
Deals long range, area damage to ground units. Side hustles as a grilled cheese sandwich food truck on weekends.
Invisible until he attacks! Moves very fast and carries a box of crickets to mask his footsteps. So sneaky.
Briefly stuns enemies with each punch. Enjoys a good brawl almost as much as a soft bamboo tank top.
Shoots a jet of flame at short range, effective against groups of enemies. Always looking for a new audience to roast with his stand-up routine.
Deals area damage up close with his nunchucks, which double as drumsticks when playing for his smooth jazz band Hot Potato.
Deals area damage at very long range. Fun.
They come in pairs, like socks, but are less friendly to your feet. Deals area damage to nearby ground units.
Deals more area damage than a Mine, but in a smaller radius. It's da bomb!
Block pathways and guide enemy ground troops... TO THEIR DOOM! Ahahaha!
Targets air and ground at long range with lethal efficiency. Another Henchman making Mother proud.
Its barrels spin fast, then faster, then fastest! Perfect for taking down big targets. Meanwhile, the Henchman says “Aaaaaaaaaaaaaaah!”
Caution! Plumbers at work. Approach at your own risk.
Freezes air and ground units... and gravity apparently!? Cool, huh?
Shoots a human-size ball of plasma that passes through and damages all enemies in its path! Range is from long to very very very long.
Pops up, zaps multiple targets at once, then slinks away. Dreams of becoming a disco ball one day.
Launches homing rockets from a questionably small silo in the ground. Effective against a trio of units.
Armed with tasers that slow and a strong desire to please Mother, they won't stop until you're toast. Burnt toast.
Flies over obstacles and drops bombs from its steel jaws – look out below! Piloted by a 7-foot Henchman who didn't make the basketball team.
It's a ninja in a box, but if you get close... it becomes a ninja out of a box!
Surprise! It's your birthday. Your final birthday.
You will get supplies delivered to this spot.

All eggs should not be put in one basket.
Not all that glows is silver.
Not worth it to go further than the sea for fish.
One shouldn't make a bull out of a fly.
An accident won't arrive with a bell on its neck.
An old dog doesn't bark lies.
I do not recognize his achievements as almost anything
A barking dog does not bite.
What is acquired easily is lost easily.
Big fish are worth of fishing even if you don't catch one.
A poke in the eye for those, who dwell on the past.
Who promises a lot, gives a little.
When you flee from a wolf, you run into a bear.
A soldier will fight long and hard for a bit of colored ribbon.
In a country according to its customs.
One sleeps like one makes his bed.
The forest answers in the same way one shouts at it.
One's own help is the best help.
Helping yourself is the best way to help yourself.
Iron must be forged when it is hot.
Better a bitter truth than a sweet lie.
Better one hazel grouse in the bag, than ten on the branch.
A beloved child has many names.
The mouth lies, but the eyes tell the truth.
A tree is climbed from its base.
Nobody who ever gave his best regretted it.
One doesn't recognize the really important moments in one's life until it's too late.
The bitterest tears shed over graves are for words left unsaid and deeds left undone.
Regrets are idle; yet history is one long regret. Everything might have turned out so differently.
Soldiers usually win the battles and generals get the credit for them.
A soldier will fight long and hard for a bit of colored ribbon.
Old soldiers never die; they just fade away.
Everyone knows what can happen to soldiers who are in front line units.
A handful of soldiers is always better than a mouthful of arguments.
When goods do not cross borders, soldiers will.
The soldier's main enemy is not the opposing soldier, but his own commander.
Be strong, believe in who you are; be strong, believe in what you feel.
Do not pray for easy lives. Pray to be stronger men.
Flexibility makes buildings to be stronger, imagine what it can do to your soul.
Pain is temporary- The pain you feel today is only to get strength to face tomorrow.
Life is, at times, tough. And all we need to do is to prove that we are tougher than it.
When you come to the end of your rope, tie a knot and hang on.

So what did he tell you about us...? And can you really trust a dude in a dinosaur costume? We've seen him eat PB&J sandwiches in there.
Hello again. You wanna get mega rich, huh? We can help. Just sign here … We'll take your silence as a non-verbal agreement.
What's more valuable than gold? LOTS of gold. There's a global gold rush happening and you don't want to miss out.
Getting mega rich ain't easy, but we've got a few tricks to share. Start by joining an active Team, OK?
Firstly, be a good Teammate – chatty, friendly, etc. Earn their trust, ya know?
Secondly, donate to their bonus defense research. You gotta spend gold to make gold.
Thirdly, join your Team's Daily Domination. This is where you can scoop up a lot more gold, and fame.
Now that we've helped you, you will help us. Just like it says in our agreement. We'll be in touch.
Someone has stolen the manuscript for our next archaeology novel. It's called Dig Lemon Boat Ages. We need it back.
We've found the manuscript. There's jam on it. Probably Bearman. Find out what else he took; check his pockets.
Just a peanut and some floss? …
